        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>May 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am not a little ashamed of myself for all the trouble I have given you: I write now to confess my sins, &amp; say that in despair I have given up the siphon-plan: and intend only to make an ordinary tank, of no very great diameter with pump.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I called at Burgess &amp; Keys &amp; found that the coated Hose was flat &amp; of course w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. not do for suction: &amp; that the gutta Percha w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> not stand frequent moving. Hence there was nothing left but the Leather &amp; this would have cost me nearly <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>20,—a sum which I grudged, especially as it, the Leather Hose, it seems, requires care &amp;c.— The only apology I can make for all the trouble I have given, is, that I was bonâ fide in strong earnest, when I wrote to you, on the scheme.</p>
<p>With thanks, pray believe me, my dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.4 coated] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.7 the Leather] ‘the’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>’</note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.8 that I] ‘I’ <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD recorded the expenses of the construction of a tank and of gutta percha pipes in his Classed account book (Down House MS). <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2821.xml">Isaac Withers Laslett</ref>, the builder in Down village, was paid £32 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on 22 April 1853 and £40 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 4 July. Gutta percha pipes cost CD £1 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and £1 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 17 June and 18 August, respectively.</note>
        </div>        
            
